The paper discusses the characteristics of recommendations generated by two methods for collaborative filtering recommenders in scholarly digital libraries, which involves information retrieval (IR) and data mining techniques. The paper also mentions the use of semantic vectors, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
